1
00:00:17,039 --> 00:00:20,359
Are you Lin, the manager
of the basketball club?

2
00:00:22,800 --> 00:00:24,160
Yes, ma'am.

3
00:01:35,239 --> 00:01:37,760
(The Rebound)

4
00:01:37,879 --> 00:01:40,760
(Directed by Tanwarin Sukkhapisit)

5
00:01:41,959 --> 00:01:44,000
Here you are, sir.

6
00:01:44,439 --> 00:01:45,439
Thank you.

7
00:01:47,200 --> 00:01:48,200
Hang on.

8
00:01:48,599 --> 00:01:49,640
Have a seat.

9
00:01:51,239 --> 00:01:52,239
What?

10
00:01:54,200 --> 00:01:55,239
Are you tired?

11
00:01:57,120 --> 00:01:58,280
No.

12
00:01:59,319 --> 00:02:01,598
What's the rush?
There are plenty of servers.

13
00:02:01,599 --> 00:02:02,959
Sit here so I can watch your face.

14
00:02:06,879 --> 00:02:08,530
They're preparing coffee.

15
00:02:09,199 --> 00:02:10,960
Come on. Stay for a bit.

16
00:02:11,319 --> 00:02:13,639
I should go and help them.

17
00:02:15,439 --> 00:02:17,090
Are you going to defy your customer?

18
00:02:20,810 --> 00:02:22,960
Give that a try. I'll unwrap
the straw for you.

19
00:02:25,599 --> 00:02:29,000
This is cocoa, very tasty.
Our specialty.

20
00:02:29,530 --> 00:02:30,530
You should try.

21
00:02:31,840 --> 00:02:32,960
Is it less sweet?

22
00:02:33,159 --> 00:02:35,719
Of course. It's like... 25 percent.

23
00:02:36,240 --> 00:02:38,439
It seems the staff here
are very attentive.

24
00:02:50,439 --> 00:02:51,919
I bet that's 50 percent sweet.

25
00:02:52,639 --> 00:02:54,599
It's definitely only 25 sweet,

26
00:02:55,120 --> 00:02:57,319
but then I also added
love which is another 25.

27
00:02:57,479 --> 00:02:58,879
So that adds up to 50.

28
00:02:59,960 --> 00:03:02,680
I'll give it 55
since you're way too cute.

29
00:03:02,919 --> 00:03:04,120
Fifty-five?

30
00:03:10,919 --> 00:03:11,919
Pay up.

31
00:03:12,879 --> 00:03:14,719
I told you.
This guy's the real deal.

32
00:03:15,159 --> 00:03:17,719
I never make mistakes
with this kind of thing.

33
00:03:18,560 --> 00:03:19,560
Take it.

34
00:03:21,520 --> 00:03:22,960
We're at work, and there's
a bunch of people here!

35
00:03:33,080 --> 00:03:34,159
What's up, Lin?

36
00:03:34,360 --> 00:03:35,360
Ryu,

37
00:03:35,520 --> 00:03:38,240
I need your help
with something important.

38
00:03:58,879 --> 00:03:59,960
Mom?

39
00:04:15,919 --> 00:04:18,050
You probably wouldn't have come
if I'd called you myself, would you?

40
00:04:18,839 --> 00:04:19,839
Mom.

41
00:04:20,120 --> 00:04:22,170
Why do you have to
live such a risky life?

42
00:04:22,240 --> 00:04:24,480
What if something happened to you?
What would I do?

43
00:04:25,560 --> 00:04:27,050
What exactly do you want?

44
00:04:27,730 --> 00:04:29,319
Playtime is over.

45
00:04:29,639 --> 00:04:30,959
It's time to come home now.

46
00:04:31,279 --> 00:04:32,610
I don't call that place home.

47
00:04:32,680 --> 00:04:34,360
So where is your home then?

48
00:04:34,839 --> 00:04:37,240
That shoebox of an apartment?

49
00:04:38,519 --> 00:04:41,199
Or that boy's house? Zen, is it?

50
00:04:47,360 --> 00:04:50,879
Do you really want me
to answer that question?

51
00:04:54,920 --> 00:04:55,920
Ryu!

52
00:04:56,639 --> 00:04:57,639
Ryu!

53
00:05:06,240 --> 00:05:08,800
Ryu, how did it go?
You met your mom, didn't you?

54
00:05:08,959 --> 00:05:10,399
Why did you trick me?

55
00:05:11,759 --> 00:05:13,800
I'm sorry. Well...

56
00:05:14,000 --> 00:05:15,920
she said she wanted to see you.

57
00:05:16,120 --> 00:05:17,920
She hadn't seen you in a long time.

58
00:05:17,959 --> 00:05:19,800
She even went looking
for you at the club.

59
00:05:19,959 --> 00:05:20,959
And?

60
00:05:21,680 --> 00:05:23,800
So you set me up so I'd talk to her?

61
00:05:24,240 --> 00:05:26,360
No, I just wanted to help.

62
00:05:26,480 --> 00:05:27,519
You wanted to help?

63
00:05:28,319 --> 00:05:30,399
Have you ever asked me
if I needed your help?

64
00:05:30,639 --> 00:05:32,279
Ryu, calm down.

65
00:05:32,600 --> 00:05:33,959
She meant well.

66
00:05:34,279 --> 00:05:35,560
But I didn't ask for it.

67
00:05:38,959 --> 00:05:40,800
I'm sorry... Ryu!

68
00:06:25,360 --> 00:06:27,439
Hang on tight or you might fall off.

69
00:06:29,360 --> 00:06:31,600
Thanks for keeping me company.

70
00:06:50,959 --> 00:06:52,199
Feeling any better now?

71
00:06:56,399 --> 00:06:58,720
Why am I such a horrible person?

72
00:07:00,720 --> 00:07:01,720
You're not.

73
00:07:02,279 --> 00:07:04,639
You didn't know what was going on
between Ryu and his mom.

74
00:07:05,240 --> 00:07:08,600
Besides, people are nosy anyway.

75
00:07:10,519 --> 00:07:12,759
How am I going to look him
in the face from now on?

76
00:07:14,639 --> 00:07:16,199
Well, if you can't
look him in the face,

77
00:07:16,399 --> 00:07:17,680
then look at his hands or feet.

78
00:07:18,360 --> 00:07:19,560
First.

79
00:07:20,199 --> 00:07:21,279
I'm serious.

80
00:07:21,920 --> 00:07:24,319
I don't think he's one
to hold grudges for that long.

81
00:07:38,720 --> 00:07:41,040
Grandma, I'm home.

82
00:07:41,279 --> 00:07:44,439
How are you? Have you eaten
anything? Are you hungry?

83
00:07:46,160 --> 00:07:47,360
I'm good, Grandma.

84
00:07:47,920 --> 00:07:51,319
Right. Do you mind staying
with Atom for a bit?

85
00:07:51,439 --> 00:07:53,519
I have to get some more desserts
from the back to add to this.

86
00:07:53,560 --> 00:07:54,639
It's not enough.

87
00:07:55,759 --> 00:07:56,879
Do you need a hand?

88
00:07:56,920 --> 00:07:59,160
It's okay.
Stay with Atom, all right?

89
00:08:00,680 --> 00:08:02,040
Watch your step.

90
00:08:02,959 --> 00:08:04,040
I'll be fine.

91
00:08:06,720 --> 00:08:07,920
What's up, Atom?

92
00:08:09,079 --> 00:08:10,720
I came to help Grandma
make desserts.

93
00:08:10,959 --> 00:08:12,360
I hope you don't mind.

94
00:08:13,319 --> 00:08:14,759
Why would I mind?

95
00:08:14,959 --> 00:08:18,319
It's good you've been visiting,
so Grandma won't feel lonely.

96
00:08:20,959 --> 00:08:22,800
Right, Zen.

97
00:08:23,079 --> 00:08:25,959
You still owe me a movie.
Should we go?

98
00:08:27,560 --> 00:08:28,560
Uh...

99
00:08:29,920 --> 00:08:30,920
Well...

100
00:08:31,639 --> 00:08:33,159
I have something to tell you.

101
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:35,210
About what?

102
00:08:36,210 --> 00:08:37,399
The thing is...

103
00:08:38,330 --> 00:08:39,330
me and...

104
00:08:41,120 --> 00:08:42,240
Grandma!

105
00:08:43,960 --> 00:08:45,039
- Grandma!
- Grandma!

106
00:08:45,159 --> 00:08:46,759
Atom, call an ambulance now!

107
00:08:47,879 --> 00:08:48,879
Grandma!

108
00:09:06,679 --> 00:09:09,090
I came straightaway
as soon as you told me.

109
00:09:11,120 --> 00:09:12,559
What did the doctor say, Zen?

110
00:09:32,639 --> 00:09:33,960
What I'm worried about is

111
00:09:34,090 --> 00:09:36,919
the thyrotoxicosis she has.

112
00:09:37,450 --> 00:09:40,759
What kind of treatment
does she need?

113
00:09:41,399 --> 00:09:44,879
She needs immediate thyroid surgery.

114
00:09:45,480 --> 00:09:46,840
Surgery?

115
00:09:47,919 --> 00:09:51,450
Exactly.
But there's no need to worry.

116
00:09:51,559 --> 00:09:55,210
It's actually normal
for someone with this condition.

117
00:09:55,399 --> 00:09:59,919
She's also been taking antithyroid
medication for two years,

118
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:01,639
but her condition hasn't improved.

119
00:10:06,039 --> 00:10:08,120
My grandmother's been sick
for a while now?

120
00:10:48,759 --> 00:10:49,759
Zen,

121
00:10:50,159 --> 00:10:51,240
what's wrong with her?

122
00:11:07,639 --> 00:11:11,039
Who's this?
What's this crybaby doing here?

123
00:11:22,720 --> 00:11:23,799
Grandma,

124
00:11:25,639 --> 00:11:27,240
I'm sorry.

125
00:11:32,200 --> 00:11:34,879
I had no idea you were sick.

126
00:11:36,360 --> 00:11:38,720
There's nothing wrong with me.

127
00:11:42,799 --> 00:11:45,639
There are still a lot of your games
that I need to watch.

128
00:11:46,320 --> 00:11:47,519
Easy-peasy.

129
00:12:01,159 --> 00:12:02,360
There, there.

130
00:12:03,320 --> 00:12:06,039
Don't cry, my little monkey.

131
00:12:09,080 --> 00:12:10,559
I love you, Grandma.

132
00:12:13,840 --> 00:12:17,159
- I love you.
- I love you too, Zen.

133
00:12:18,559 --> 00:12:20,360
There, there. Don't cry.

134
00:12:30,399 --> 00:12:32,120
It's 120,000 for the surgery?

135
00:12:35,679 --> 00:12:38,919
Have you thought
about what you're going to do?

136
00:12:40,840 --> 00:12:43,360
I have to find money for Grandma's
surgery no matter what.

137
00:12:46,320 --> 00:12:47,360
Zen,

138
00:12:47,480 --> 00:12:50,720
I have a bit on me.
You can take it for now.

139
00:12:50,799 --> 00:12:51,799
Me too.

140
00:12:53,320 --> 00:12:55,360
Hey, it's okay.

141
00:12:56,080 --> 00:12:57,200
I'll...

142
00:12:57,759 --> 00:12:59,559
I'll find a way.

143
00:13:06,600 --> 00:13:08,080
Zen, Ryu...

144
00:13:12,559 --> 00:13:13,559
Street basketball?

145
00:13:14,039 --> 00:13:15,440
Three-on-three.

146
00:13:15,600 --> 00:13:18,159
You'll get 150,000 if you win.

147
00:13:24,200 --> 00:13:25,240
Who's with me?

148
00:13:26,559 --> 00:13:27,559
I am.

149
00:13:28,320 --> 00:13:30,559
I'm a street basketball veteran.
You can trust me with this.

150
00:13:30,679 --> 00:13:31,840
Zen, what about you?

151
00:13:35,960 --> 00:13:36,960
Mm.

152
00:13:37,919 --> 00:13:39,159
Let's win some money.

153
00:13:46,399 --> 00:13:47,559
We have to pull this off.

154
00:13:55,799 --> 00:13:57,720
Are you really going
to play street basketball?

155
00:13:59,000 --> 00:14:00,039
Mm.

156
00:14:00,200 --> 00:14:01,559
With Ryu and that moro...

157
00:14:02,159 --> 00:14:03,159
and Atom?

158
00:14:03,320 --> 00:14:04,320
Mm.

159
00:14:04,960 --> 00:14:06,360
Ryu, are you sure?

160
00:14:06,720 --> 00:14:07,759
You and...

161
00:14:09,399 --> 00:14:10,399
and Atom?

162
00:14:10,519 --> 00:14:11,519
Of course.

163
00:14:12,120 --> 00:14:13,600
I won't whack him in the face.

164
00:14:13,759 --> 00:14:16,200
If you don't start,
then I won't retaliate.

165
00:14:18,480 --> 00:14:19,639
Like I said,

166
00:14:20,120 --> 00:14:21,600
Atom's going to be training with us.

167
00:14:22,039 --> 00:14:25,200
But he'll train after we're done

168
00:14:26,600 --> 00:14:27,799
so you guys won't be confused.

169
00:14:28,000 --> 00:14:29,799
- Hm.
- Mm.

170
00:14:30,559 --> 00:14:32,039
I look forward
to training with you guys.

171
00:14:35,039 --> 00:14:37,240
Where's Lin? Isn't she here yet?

172
00:14:40,279 --> 00:14:42,360
Jedi, do you know anything?

173
00:14:42,759 --> 00:14:44,240
No idea.

174
00:14:44,360 --> 00:14:45,919
She didn't text me or anything.

175
00:14:46,559 --> 00:14:48,240
She had to deal
with something about her family.

176
00:14:49,159 --> 00:14:50,240
Oh.

177
00:14:52,480 --> 00:14:54,000
Come on. Let's do it.

178
00:14:54,080 --> 00:14:57,039
Hey.

179
00:14:57,679 --> 00:14:59,759
- Let's play.
- Hey, wait for me.

180
00:15:00,200 --> 00:15:02,039
All right. Let's go.

181
00:15:05,919 --> 00:15:07,759
- Hey.
- Hey!

182
00:15:08,480 --> 00:15:09,480
Hey.

183
00:15:09,919 --> 00:15:11,000
Game on.

184
00:15:20,440 --> 00:15:22,480
- Ryu.
- Come on, Ryu.

185
00:15:23,360 --> 00:15:24,360
Hey.

186
00:15:27,120 --> 00:15:28,120
Zen!

187
00:15:28,919 --> 00:15:29,919
Are you okay?

188
00:15:30,480 --> 00:15:31,480
I'm fine.

189
00:15:31,480 --> 00:15:32,480
I'll give you a hand.

190
00:15:32,559 --> 00:15:33,559
I'll do it.

191
00:15:44,039 --> 00:15:45,080
Let's keep practicing.

192
00:15:46,120 --> 00:15:47,120
So?

193
00:15:57,639 --> 00:15:59,159
- Help him.
- Keep going.

194
00:16:00,960 --> 00:16:02,519
Come on.

195
00:16:06,279 --> 00:16:07,679
Are you done with your thing?

196
00:16:07,840 --> 00:16:09,840
Mm. All done.

197
00:16:10,639 --> 00:16:12,159
But I thought practice
would be over by now.

198
00:16:12,840 --> 00:16:15,720
It is over. Those guys are training
for street basketball.

199
00:16:17,120 --> 00:16:18,240
Street basketball?

200
00:16:18,960 --> 00:16:20,240
Why?

201
00:16:20,960 --> 00:16:24,240
Isn't this wasting the team's
time and effort?

202
00:16:24,879 --> 00:16:26,039
That won't do.

203
00:16:26,960 --> 00:16:28,200
I should tell Dad.

204
00:16:28,600 --> 00:16:29,639
Hold it.

205
00:16:29,799 --> 00:16:32,080
They're playing to pay
for Zen's grandma's surgery.

206
00:16:32,519 --> 00:16:33,840
She's sick.

207
00:16:34,159 --> 00:16:35,360
Zen's grandma is sick.

208
00:16:35,559 --> 00:16:37,919
That's right. She needs a surgery.

209
00:16:38,240 --> 00:16:39,679
So they decided they'd play.

210
00:16:40,039 --> 00:16:42,960
But judging by their form,
I don't think they'll make it.

211
00:17:07,890 --> 00:17:09,170
What are you guys playing at?

212
00:17:10,680 --> 00:17:11,680
Coach,

213
00:17:12,170 --> 00:17:15,079
I'm sorry I didn't tell you
about using the court.

214
00:17:15,920 --> 00:17:17,920
- We're about to...
- The prize money.

215
00:17:20,170 --> 00:17:21,170
You have to win it.

216
00:17:22,079 --> 00:17:24,559
Whether it's the second
or third place, bring it home.

217
00:17:24,720 --> 00:17:25,920
And I'll pay the rest.

218
00:17:27,119 --> 00:17:28,440
But Coach...

219
00:17:28,559 --> 00:17:30,680
What's there to be confused about?
Keep training.

220
00:17:31,920 --> 00:17:33,170
- Yes, Coach!
- Yes, Coach!

221
00:17:39,119 --> 00:17:40,650
- Come on.
- Let's do it.

222
00:17:47,519 --> 00:17:50,079
Who's your daughter?
You're such a cool dad.

223
00:17:51,000 --> 00:17:52,000
Naturally.

224
00:18:01,440 --> 00:18:02,650
Hey, hey!

225
00:18:03,599 --> 00:18:06,279
Ryu, why are you
showing off your dribbling?

226
00:18:06,650 --> 00:18:08,839
You got past his defense,
so take the shot!

227
00:18:09,720 --> 00:18:10,759
Again.

228
00:18:11,410 --> 00:18:12,559
- Yes, Coach!
- Yes, Coach!

229
00:18:13,200 --> 00:18:14,200
Come on.

230
00:18:23,359 --> 00:18:24,359
See?

231
00:18:28,920 --> 00:18:30,079
Trust.

232
00:18:30,890 --> 00:18:33,039
That's your issue.

233
00:18:34,200 --> 00:18:35,200
Therefore,

234
00:18:36,759 --> 00:18:38,170
let's try it this way.

235
00:18:42,650 --> 00:18:45,680
You have to pass the ball
as usual but blindfolded.

236
00:18:46,960 --> 00:18:48,200
You have to pull this off.

237
00:18:49,039 --> 00:18:50,200
- Yes, Coach!
- Yes, Coach!

238
00:18:54,200 --> 00:18:56,240
Here. We'll start with you, Atom.

239
00:19:02,720 --> 00:19:03,720
Zen.

240
00:19:08,039 --> 00:19:09,079
Failed.

241
00:19:10,720 --> 00:19:11,720
Try again.

242
00:19:17,359 --> 00:19:18,359
Ryu.

243
00:19:23,890 --> 00:19:24,890
Failed.

244
00:19:26,599 --> 00:19:27,799
Try again, Ryu.

245
00:19:34,319 --> 00:19:35,319
Atom.

246
00:19:39,359 --> 00:19:40,359
Listen.

247
00:19:40,650 --> 00:19:41,920
You have to listen to each other.

248
00:19:42,359 --> 00:19:44,599
Make good use of your senses!

249
00:19:44,960 --> 00:19:46,200
- Yes, Coach!
- Yes, Coach!

250
00:19:48,079 --> 00:19:50,039
Here. One more time.

251
00:20:03,079 --> 00:20:04,079
Better.

252
00:20:09,170 --> 00:20:10,200
Ryu.

253
00:20:14,119 --> 00:20:15,119
Atom.

254
00:20:34,519 --> 00:20:37,200
Three-on-three street basketball!

255
00:20:37,279 --> 00:20:40,039
The first team is RAZ!

256
00:20:40,170 --> 00:20:42,519
And the second team is LEB!

257
00:20:42,559 --> 00:20:45,170
Give it up!

258
00:20:45,410 --> 00:20:47,410
Let's go! Let's go!

259
00:20:47,559 --> 00:20:49,440
Come on, Zen!

260
00:20:52,170 --> 00:20:54,039
There's not much distance at all!

261
00:20:54,170 --> 00:20:57,480
They're breathing
down each other's necks!

262
00:20:57,559 --> 00:20:59,279
Ryu has the ball,

263
00:20:59,410 --> 00:21:01,519
and he's running though!

264
00:21:03,079 --> 00:21:07,410
Let's have a look at LEB!
They're really in the zone!

265
00:21:07,480 --> 00:21:10,759
They're plowing through!
Zen intercepts! He scores!

266
00:21:10,890 --> 00:21:12,440
Wow!

267
00:21:12,519 --> 00:21:19,200
RAZ is really causing a lot
of problems for LEB's defense!

268
00:21:19,279 --> 00:21:20,559
Let's keep watching!

269
00:21:20,960 --> 00:21:22,039
Go! Go!

270
00:21:22,119 --> 00:21:25,278
Whoa! And they scored again!

271
00:21:25,279 --> 00:21:26,519
That's it.

272
00:21:27,279 --> 00:21:31,169
LEB say they're also tough
and here to play.

273
00:21:31,170 --> 00:21:32,920
They're going head-to-head!

274
00:21:33,170 --> 00:21:38,410
All right. Here it comes.
What a beautiful shot!

275
00:21:38,480 --> 00:21:44,650
