296
00:23:07,000 --> 00:23:10,240
- Ryu!
- You can't win if you don't fight.

297
00:23:10,319 --> 00:23:12,079
And he scores!

298
00:23:12,160 --> 00:23:15,519
I can tell this is a tough one for
RAZ.

299
00:23:16,119 --> 00:23:17,480
And the ball goes to Ryu.

300
00:23:17,559 --> 00:23:20,680
That's his specialty!

301
00:23:20,799 --> 00:23:22,240
How are they going to counter
that now?

302
00:23:22,279 --> 00:23:23,559
- Ryu!
- RAZ is on fire.

303
00:23:23,680 --> 00:23:27,039
NewGen is known for being swift.

304
00:23:27,119 --> 00:23:30,480
If it's a swift playstyle,
it's them.

305
00:23:30,599 --> 00:23:34,880
It seems NewGen
has got them figured out.

306
00:23:34,960 --> 00:23:36,480
But they're still behind...

307
00:23:36,720 --> 00:23:40,160
Coach, one more game
and they win the tournament.

308
00:23:42,319 --> 00:23:43,920
- Jedi.
- Yes, Coach?

309
00:23:44,440 --> 00:23:45,839
The next one is the final, isn't it?

310
00:23:45,920 --> 00:23:46,920
Yes, it is.

311
00:23:47,720 --> 00:23:49,759
Based on my observations,

312
00:23:49,880 --> 00:23:51,599
our team is more exhausted
than usual.

313
00:23:52,880 --> 00:23:53,880
Lin,

314
00:23:54,559 --> 00:23:57,119
what's the difference between
first and second place?

315
00:23:58,039 --> 00:24:01,039
First place gets 150,000,
and second place gets 80,000.

316
00:24:01,799 --> 00:24:05,279
How much do they need
for the surgery?

317
00:24:05,359 --> 00:24:06,680
It's 120,000, Coach.

318
00:24:09,759 --> 00:24:11,839
They can't give up now!
The ball goes to Zen!

319
00:24:11,920 --> 00:24:13,200
And Zen...

320
00:24:13,759 --> 00:24:15,839
Gee, that was so close!

321
00:24:16,880 --> 00:24:20,559
Zen shoots again,
and he scores! All right!

322
00:24:21,079 --> 00:24:24,599
This is intense. And NewGen...

323
00:24:25,160 --> 00:24:31,400
Whoa! And they did it
for the second time!

324
00:24:31,640 --> 00:24:34,559
And this one's from NewGen!

325
00:24:34,640 --> 00:24:38,799
That's their trick! And they score!

326
00:24:39,039 --> 00:24:41,960
Ryu has the ball. He's feinting.

327
00:24:42,359 --> 00:24:45,000
And then... wow!

328
00:24:45,559 --> 00:24:46,559
He got through!

329
00:24:46,720 --> 00:24:49,200
All on his own!

330
00:24:49,359 --> 00:24:51,160
NewGen shoots.

331
00:24:51,720 --> 00:24:52,960
Whoa.

332
00:24:53,519 --> 00:24:55,839
Match point!
Who's going to score this one?

333
00:24:55,920 --> 00:24:58,799
And they did it!

334
00:24:58,920 --> 00:25:04,880
And RAZ goes to the final! Wow!

335
00:25:04,960 --> 00:25:07,480
Stay tuned to see who they're facing

336
00:25:07,559 --> 00:25:09,519
and which team's going
to get the trophy

337
00:25:09,599 --> 00:25:12,440
and the prize money
totaling 150,000 baht.

338
00:25:12,519 --> 00:25:13,720
- Let's go!
- Let's keep watching.

339
00:25:13,880 --> 00:25:17,279
Our first team are
the newbie underdogs.

340
00:25:17,359 --> 00:25:21,480
But I'm not sure if their exhaustion
from a whole day of playing

341
00:25:21,559 --> 00:25:23,480
will affect them or not.

342
00:25:23,559 --> 00:25:27,960
So stay tuned and
keep rooting for RAZ!

343
00:25:28,759 --> 00:25:31,200
Go! Go! Go!

344
00:25:39,720 --> 00:25:41,400
As for the opposing team...

345
00:25:41,519 --> 00:25:45,400
Look at that. There are no words
to describe them.

346
00:25:45,480 --> 00:25:48,119
They're three-time champions.
Give it up for...

347
00:25:48,519 --> 00:25:51,920
King James!

348
00:25:58,519 --> 00:26:00,640
Wow!

349
00:26:04,039 --> 00:26:07,240
It's definitely going
to be a rough night!

350
00:26:07,920 --> 00:26:11,039
That's James!
He's on the youth national team.

351
00:26:12,160 --> 00:26:13,240
Shoot.

352
00:26:13,799 --> 00:26:15,599
The guys are in for some trouble.

353
00:26:16,240 --> 00:26:18,720
I thought he looked familiar.
Are they going to be okay?

354
00:26:22,759 --> 00:26:26,359
I guarantee this game
will not disappoint, guys!

355
00:26:28,920 --> 00:26:31,039
Come on! Keep it up!

356
00:26:33,279 --> 00:26:34,519
Hang in there, Ryu!

357
00:26:35,400 --> 00:26:36,480
Hey, Atom!

358
00:26:37,279 --> 00:26:39,039
Do it, Atom!

359
00:26:40,039 --> 00:26:42,440
Come on, Ryu.

360
00:26:43,119 --> 00:26:46,160
Shoot! Take the shot!

361
00:26:47,480 --> 00:26:49,440
Calm down! Keep it together!

362
00:26:52,079 --> 00:26:53,519
Shoot!

363
00:26:57,319 --> 00:26:58,440
Take it easy.

364
00:27:02,279 --> 00:27:03,400
- Ryu.
- Ryu!

365
00:27:03,480 --> 00:27:04,680
Whoa.

366
00:27:10,359 --> 00:27:13,640
This is super brutal.

367
00:27:13,839 --> 00:27:16,799
It's neck-and-neck.

368
00:27:17,640 --> 00:27:21,400
He shoots. He scores!

369
00:27:21,839 --> 00:27:23,200
RAZ!

370
00:27:23,359 --> 00:27:26,119
RAZ! RAZ!

371
00:27:26,240 --> 00:27:27,759
RAZ!

372
00:27:27,839 --> 00:27:29,160
Whoa!

373
00:27:29,440 --> 00:27:31,000
They let that one through.

374
00:27:31,079 --> 00:27:33,720
RAZ appears to need a timeout.

375
00:27:33,799 --> 00:27:38,319
See? They didn't get their nickname
because they were lucky.

376
00:27:38,400 --> 00:27:41,079
King James is still
living up to their name.

377
00:27:41,160 --> 00:27:45,039
Let's find out how RAZ
is going rebound from this.

378
00:27:45,680 --> 00:27:47,160
I know you're all tired.

379
00:27:48,480 --> 00:27:49,720
But you're nearly there now.

380
00:27:50,759 --> 00:27:53,960
You're playing like
you usually play.

381
00:27:54,680 --> 00:27:55,960
But this is street basketball.

382
00:27:56,640 --> 00:27:58,559
Since they're playing street style,

383
00:27:59,400 --> 00:28:00,640
then you have to as well.

384
00:28:01,680 --> 00:28:03,599
If they push, you have to push back.

385
00:28:04,200 --> 00:28:05,400
What is there to be scared of?

386
00:28:06,920 --> 00:28:08,119
Get your head in the game.

387
00:28:09,440 --> 00:28:11,319
- Yes, Coach.
- Yes, Coach.

388
00:28:12,400 --> 00:28:14,640
Come on. Bring it in.

389
00:28:15,119 --> 00:28:16,319
Bring it in.

390
00:28:17,000 --> 00:28:18,000
Together.

391
00:28:19,000 --> 00:28:21,759
RAZ! Hey!

392
00:28:23,240 --> 00:28:25,400
Go! Go! Go!

393
00:28:27,200 --> 00:28:28,440
Let's do it!

394
00:28:31,599 --> 00:28:33,599
Stop them!

395
00:28:34,160 --> 00:28:35,160
Over here!

396
00:28:36,039 --> 00:28:37,079
Take the shot!

397
00:28:37,279 --> 00:28:38,880
A three-pointer!

398
00:28:39,240 --> 00:28:40,240
Well done!

399
00:28:44,279 --> 00:28:47,640
Wow! This is so gut-wrenching!

400
00:28:47,720 --> 00:28:49,519
There's only one minute left!

401
00:28:49,640 --> 00:28:52,680
We'll find out soon enough if
the reigning champions

402
00:28:52,759 --> 00:28:56,920
will be able to secure
their fourth championship or not.

403
00:29:09,200 --> 00:29:10,640
You three, listen!

404
00:29:18,039 --> 00:29:20,839
Trust. That's your issue.

405
00:29:21,000 --> 00:29:25,079
We will focus on listening
and sensing each other's movement.

406
00:29:25,400 --> 00:29:27,640
Make good use of your senses!

407
00:30:00,160 --> 00:30:01,200
Grandma,

408
00:30:01,880 --> 00:30:03,160
please wait for me.

409
00:30:26,359 --> 00:30:29,000
RAZ!

410
00:31:11,359 --> 00:31:12,359
Grandma?

411
00:31:16,000 --> 00:31:17,000
Grandma!

412
00:31:17,519 --> 00:31:20,119
The doctor said you're not supposed
to use your voice after surgery.

413
00:31:20,559 --> 00:31:21,960
Don't speak just yet.

414
00:31:23,319 --> 00:31:24,880
Not just yet.

415
00:31:26,759 --> 00:31:27,759
Okay?

416
00:31:29,960 --> 00:31:32,440
Oh? The phone?

417
00:31:37,880 --> 00:31:38,920
Here you go.

418
00:31:39,559 --> 00:31:40,559
Take it slow.

419
00:31:52,519 --> 00:31:56,039
(Are you tired? I'm sorry
for being a burden.)

420
00:32:02,200 --> 00:32:03,759
Not at all, Grandma.

421
00:32:12,160 --> 00:32:13,759
I'm not tired.

422
00:32:14,920 --> 00:32:16,359
I told you.

423
00:32:17,359 --> 00:32:19,200
I'd take care of you.

424
00:32:24,599 --> 00:32:26,480
But don't worry, Grandma.

425
00:32:26,759 --> 00:32:28,799
Even though Mom and Dad
aren't here anymore,

426
00:32:28,880 --> 00:32:30,480
I'll look after you.

427
00:32:41,799 --> 00:32:43,559
Stay with me for a long time, okay?

428
00:33:03,920 --> 00:33:07,359
It's nice the three of us
got to play together.

429
00:33:10,400 --> 00:33:11,519
I agree.

430
00:33:12,640 --> 00:33:14,359
You're an awesome partner.

431
00:33:19,519 --> 00:33:20,680
Same goes for you.

432
00:33:21,640 --> 00:33:25,640
The game reminded me
about something.

433
00:33:28,200 --> 00:33:29,279
What is it?

434
00:33:31,720 --> 00:33:33,400
The joy of shooting hoops.

435
00:33:34,359 --> 00:33:36,240
It wasn't for the sake
of the competition.

436
00:33:37,400 --> 00:33:40,039
We play because we love it.

437
00:33:40,759 --> 00:33:42,319
Basketball taught us to love others

438
00:33:42,640 --> 00:33:44,839
and helped us love ourselves again.

439
00:34:06,039 --> 00:34:07,880
The basketball team has been

440
00:34:07,960 --> 00:34:11,329
bringing our school
a lot of positive attention.

441
00:34:12,079 --> 00:34:15,960
So I'd like to propose
to the board to reconsider

442
00:34:16,119 --> 00:34:18,880
and allow the team to
continue next year.

443
00:34:20,440 --> 00:34:24,679
But we've already decided
to disband it next year.

444
00:34:25,239 --> 00:34:28,239
But we can reconsider it, can't we?

445
00:34:30,679 --> 00:34:32,769
I think we should move ahead.

446
00:34:32,880 --> 00:34:36,679
Demolishing the gym to build
a science and technology building

447
00:34:36,840 --> 00:34:40,289
is quite complicated.
There are a lot of details involved.

448
00:34:41,159 --> 00:34:43,329
But I don't see how the demolishing
and rebuilding of the building have

449
00:34:43,809 --> 00:34:46,599
anything to do with the disbanding
of the basketball team.

450
00:34:46,920 --> 00:34:50,719
And the club doesn't require
a large budget to operate.

451
00:34:52,769 --> 00:34:55,920
That's right. It's not too much.

452
00:34:57,440 --> 00:35:00,400
But you're probably well aware

453
00:35:00,920 --> 00:35:03,599
that our total budget
isn't much either.

454
00:35:04,079 --> 00:35:05,159
That's right.

455
00:35:05,239 --> 00:35:07,768
I think we should focus on
academic achievements

456
00:35:07,769 --> 00:35:09,360
according to the policy
from upper management.

457
00:35:09,400 --> 00:35:12,769
More importantly, Kanin's
students have also won

458
00:35:12,809 --> 00:35:15,679
a lot of national academic awards.

459
00:35:16,159 --> 00:35:17,559
If we provide them with proper
support,

460
00:35:17,679 --> 00:35:20,519
our students could
even win internationally.

461
00:35:26,599 --> 00:35:28,000
(Meeting Room 1)

462
00:35:29,079 --> 00:35:30,769
Don't worry, Kanin.

463
00:35:30,840 --> 00:35:33,559
We're on your side, no matter what.

464
00:35:33,769 --> 00:35:35,000
Thank you very much.

465
00:35:35,519 --> 00:35:38,159
We're a school. We have to focus on
academic achievement.

466
00:35:38,239 --> 00:35:39,809
We're doing the right thing.

467
00:35:42,159 --> 00:35:43,400
What is this?

468
00:35:43,480 --> 00:35:45,769
We're making a name for our school,

469
00:35:46,039 --> 00:35:47,840
yet they still insist
on disbanding our club?

470
00:35:49,239 --> 00:35:51,480
So we'll have to find
a new club next year?

471
00:35:51,960 --> 00:35:54,119
I won't get to play
basketball ever again?

472
00:35:55,159 --> 00:35:58,039
No, I love basketball.

473
00:35:59,809 --> 00:36:01,289
It'll be fine, Chogun.

474
00:36:05,329 --> 00:36:06,480
Should we protest?

475
00:36:06,719 --> 00:36:07,920
I'll lead.

476
00:36:11,400 --> 00:36:13,360
Good idea. I'm in.

477
00:36:14,639 --> 00:36:15,639
I'm in!

478
00:36:16,119 --> 00:36:18,289
- I'm in!
- Count me in!

479
00:36:18,360 --> 00:36:19,360
Let's do it!

480
00:36:21,079 --> 00:36:23,960
A protest is a way to express our
objection.

481
00:36:24,039 --> 00:36:25,079
Count me in too.

482
00:36:25,159 --> 00:36:26,329
- Me too.
- I want to do it too.

483
00:36:26,400 --> 00:36:28,239
- I'm in too!
- I'm in!

484
00:36:28,329 --> 00:36:29,480
Hold on!

485
00:36:30,289 --> 00:36:31,809
Calm down, guys!

486
00:36:32,239 --> 00:36:33,639
The game isn't over yet!

487
00:36:34,199 --> 00:36:36,360
We can always hope for a miracle!

488
00:36:36,809 --> 00:36:38,360
What miracle?

489
00:36:39,159 --> 00:36:41,159
Our next game has to be our best
game.

490
00:36:41,559 --> 00:36:44,769
We got to nationals.
Anything can happen.

491
00:36:45,809 --> 00:36:46,809
He's right.

492
00:36:47,239 --> 00:36:50,199
If we can pull it off, then we have
leverage against the school.

493
00:36:52,400 --> 00:36:53,519
That's true.

494
00:36:55,880 --> 00:36:57,039
But are we going
to be able to pull it off?

495
00:36:57,329 --> 00:36:59,289
It's already a miracle
we got through.

496
00:36:59,679 --> 00:37:03,439
Right? The teams in the next round
are brutal.

497
00:37:03,440 --> 00:37:04,559
Of course we can.

498
00:37:05,400 --> 00:37:06,769
We have to make it through.

499
00:37:12,239 --> 00:37:13,400
Let's do it to it, guys!

500
00:37:13,559 --> 00:37:14,880
- Let's do it to it!
- Let's do it to it!

501
00:37:15,039 --> 00:37:16,289
Yes!

502
00:37:16,360 --> 00:37:17,769
Let's do it!

503
00:37:19,329 --> 00:37:20,400
Bring it in.

504
00:37:21,119 --> 00:37:23,519
- Let's do it to it!
- Let's do it to it!

505
00:37:24,639 --> 00:37:25,880
All right!

506
00:37:30,519 --> 00:37:33,480
Wow. Why is your school
being so harsh?

507
00:37:33,880 --> 00:37:36,079
They're that bent
on disbanding the club?

508
00:37:36,679 --> 00:37:37,679
I know, right?

509
00:37:38,119 --> 00:37:39,329
I'm so bummed.

510
00:37:40,599 --> 00:37:41,920
You won't get to play

511
00:37:42,559 --> 00:37:45,400
in your senior year
without the club.

512
00:37:46,119 --> 00:37:47,920
Then what about
your university scholarship?

513
00:37:47,960 --> 00:37:49,239
What would you do about it?

514
00:37:49,599 --> 00:37:52,400
Isn't that your dream?

515
00:37:53,079 --> 00:37:54,119
Right?

516
00:37:54,519 --> 00:37:57,440
But I'll give it a go in case
the board changes their mind.

517
00:37:58,360 --> 00:38:00,920
I have to go now.
I'm visiting Grandma.

518
00:38:01,329 --> 00:38:04,599
Sure. Visit her for me too.
I'm worried about her.

519
00:38:18,960 --> 00:38:21,440
Have you read the details
about the scholarship in Phuket?

520
00:38:25,480 --> 00:38:26,559
Yes, Dad.

521
00:38:27,440 --> 00:38:29,840
Can I discuss it with the agent?

522
00:38:30,769 --> 00:38:31,840
Why?

523
00:38:33,159 --> 00:38:34,159
It's nothing.

524
00:38:40,920 --> 00:38:42,199
Free tuition,

525
00:38:43,079 --> 00:38:44,599
training incentives,

526
00:38:45,079 --> 00:38:48,809
and your monthly expenses covered
while you're on our team.

527
00:38:52,559 --> 00:38:53,840
I have one condition.

528
00:38:56,039 --> 00:38:57,159
I was expecting that.

529
00:38:58,599 --> 00:39:02,440
I didn't think an athlete of your
level would be satisfied.

530
00:39:05,119 --> 00:39:06,440
Is there anything else you want?

531
00:39:11,329 --> 00:39:12,809
If you want me to join your team,

532
00:39:13,880 --> 00:39:16,000
can you award the scholarship
to one of my friends as well?

533
00:39:18,559 --> 00:39:22,519
It also depends on his skill.

534
00:39:24,079 --> 00:39:25,440
There's no need to worry about that.

535
00:39:25,920 --> 00:39:27,809
You'll get to witness it for
yourself.

536
00:39:35,880 --> 00:39:41,039
This is the game that will decide
which team goes to the provincials.

537
00:39:41,119 --> 00:39:42,769
There is a quota of four teams.

538
00:39:42,840 --> 00:39:44,920
Three of the places
have been filled.

539
00:39:45,079 --> 00:39:50,119
